<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFF13FD68FEE9FD2C" bold="true" box="[189,294,662,688]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBE850DFE88FD68FD8DFD2C" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Lindley" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[294,578,662,688]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exasperatus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFE88FD68FD8DFD2C" box="[294,578,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">Myoxanthus exasperatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently found to apply to what had been previously known as 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBE850DFA23FD69FF3CFD48" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFA23FD69FF3CFD48" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. speciosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFFBE850DFEAFFD44FD5BFD48" author="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P." box="[257,660,698,725]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref31437" refString="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P. (2020) Revision of the Costa Rican species of Myoxanthus (Pleurothallidinae: Orchidaceae). Phytotaxa 448: 1 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 448.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans 2020</bibRefCitation>
, also see commentary under 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBE850DFC7BFD45FB64FD48" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[981,1195,698,724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parahybunensis">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFC7BFD45FB64FD48" box="[981,1195,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. parahybunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This species is easily distinguished by its caespitose habit, fully hispidulous sheaths, the ramicaul and narrow ovate leaves frequently purple suffused, flowers yellowish striped with red-purple, a column without teeth and an oblong purple-suffused lip with two longitudinal, rounded calli from the base to above the middle.
</paragraph>
